'''Russel "Buddy" Helm''' was a writer for the [[Star Wars (comic strip)|Star Wars comic strip]]. He was hired by [[Lucasfilm Ltd.|Lucasfilm's]] Lindsay Smith after artist [[Russ Manning]] could no longer script it due to illness.

A fan "urban myth" previously held that '''Russ Helm''' was a pseudonym for comic book writer [[Archie Goodwin]] when he wrote for the Star Wars newspaper strip, and that he later dropped the penname in favor of his real name starting with the story [[Han Solo at Stars' End (comic strip)|''Han Solo at Stars' End'']]. This was proven wrong in [[Star Wars Insider 141]].

